<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE'S MEDFLY SPRAYING POLICY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
My family and I feel we are in a nightmare from which there is no end. We have 
been sprayed 12 times with malathion and now we are scheduled to be sprayed 
three more times, probably all summer. 
</P>
<P>
I have a 6-month-old son and a 3-year-old daughter, and my greatest fear for 
their health is from our own state government! Our despair, anger and disgust 
are overwhelming. 
</P>
<P>
California is cutting back funds for trauma centers, schools, the disabled and 
the blind -- but it blithely spends $100 million for pesticides and 
helicopters! We have a drought in Los Angeles and can't wash our cars or water 
our yards without getting a fine, but the state can dump all the pesticides it 
wants on those same yards and cars. 
</P>
<P>
California's shortfall is not in money -- it's in morality. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN VORNHOLT 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
