<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAD GUNMEN AND OUTLAWING ASSAULT RIFLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I quote Sullum: "Yet the Jacksonville and Stockton massacres cast serious 
doubts on the notion that gun-control laws can prevent rampages by armed 
lunatics." 
</P>
<P>
If I understand Mr. Sullum, he believes that, since we can't stop all maniacs 
from buying all types of semiautomatic weapons, regulatory laws are useless. 
His logic escapes me. If gun control laws can prevent just some of the 
rampages, I shall be immensely gratified. 
</P>
<P>
NRA, take note: Guns weren't out-lawed, so Patrick Purdy and James Pough got 
guns -- assault rifles. 
</P>
<P>
RAY B. HOOD 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
