<TEXT>
<P>
I am a Japanese-American and I used to watch the Dick Tracy cartoon series when 
I was a kid growing up in the '60s. 
</P>
<P>
It did not make me a racist. Richard Katsuda of the National Coalition for 
Redress and Reparations stated: "Cartoons like this can be destructive at an 
early age." Is he serious? 
</P>
<P>
My son, 6, and my daughter, 3 1/2, both love the cartoon series! The minority 
spokespersons do not speak for me and my children; let them dictate their 
narrow-minded views to their own families. 
</P>
<P>
HENRY SAKAIDA 
