PHOTOGRAPH SEIZURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I read with shock and anger the July 5 account of the grand jury investigation 
of San Francisco photographer Jock Sturges ("Photo Lab Sets Off FBI Probe"). 
That the police can forcibly enter the home of a citizen, search and seize his 
possessions including his means of livelihood and then hold them for months 
without so much as filing charges is a chilling thought. 
</P>
