<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: RED WINGS REPLACE DEMERS WITH FORMER CAPITAL COACH MURRAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Detroit Red Wings fired Jacques Demers as coach Friday and hired former 
Washington Capital coach Bryan Murray to be both coach and general manager. 
</P>
<P>
Murray, 47, had guided the Capitals to the playoffs in seven of his nine full 
seasons, but his team never advanced past the second round. He was fired and 
replaced by his younger brother, Terry, in January. 
</P>
<P>
In four seasons under Demers, the Red Wings qualified three times for the 
playoffs, advancing twice to the semifinals before losing both times to the 
Edmonton Oilers. Last season, the Red Wings finished last in the Norris 
Division with 70 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
