<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUMMER PREP BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
PARKS' 30 LEAD MARINA PAST ROLLING HILLS, 89-71 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Center Cherokee Parks scored 30 points to lead Marina High School to an 89-71 
victory over Rolling Hills Friday in the first round of the Servite summer 
boys' basketball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Parks, who made 13 of 21 shots from the field and 4 of 6 from the free-throw 
line, had 13 rebounds and six blocked shots and scored 13 points in the first 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
In other first-round games, Long Beach Millikan defeated Servite, 86-53, 
Dominguez stopped Huntington Beach, 56-49, and Los Alamitos rolled past San 
Pasqual, 84-45. 
</P>
<P>
In consolation games, Lakewood routed Loara, 106-70, and Western got past St. 
Anthony, 85-77. In a winners' bracket quarterfinal, Long Beach Poly beat 
Woodbridge, 58-56. 
</P>
<P>
In the Mater Dei summer boys' basketball tournament at Mater Dei: 
</P>
<P>
Bret McCorkle scored seven straight points late in the fourth quarter as 
Capistrano Valley held off Artesia, the state Division II champion, 68-54. 
</P>
<P>
J.J. Ballesteros led all scorers with 21 points and Jason Janeski and DeJuan 
Matthews each had 18 to lead Mater Dei to a 114-49 victory over Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
In other first-round games, Santa Clara defeated Ocean View, 77-71, and Los 
Alamitos defeated Foothill, 70-55. In a second-round consolation game, Artesia 
defeated Ocean View, 78-63. 
</P>
</TEXT>
