<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN SEARCH OF FIRST WIN, DUKES MEET BREAKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Newport Beach Dukes try for their first victory when they host the Miami 
Beach Breakers in a Team Tennis match at 7:30 tonight at the John Wayne Tennis 
Club. 
</P>
<P>
The Dukes lost their opener, 27-23, to the Raleigh Edge Thursday. Miami Beach 
was leading Charlotte, 24-14, when the match was suspended due to rain Thursday 
in Miami. 
</P>
<P>
No current Team Tennis player has played more seasons than Miami Beach's Sandy 
Collins, an eight-year veteran of the league. 
</P>
<P>
Collins, who mostly plays doubles on the pro tour, is joined on the Breakers by 
Cammy MacGregor, Richard Schmidt and Greg Van Emburgh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
