SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police are looking for vandals who damaged the windows of at least 26 vehicles 
parked on streets in Ocean Beach and Loma Portal. 
</P>
<P>
"It just looks like someone hanging out the window and shooting cars as they go 
by," police detective Jim Yeatts said. 
</P>
<P>
The vandals apparently used a pellet gun, a BB gun or a slingshot, police 
spokesman Bill Robinson said. The windows were cracked but not smashed through. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they believed the shootings occurred sometime between 10 p.m. 
Tuesday and 8 a.m. Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Seven of the cars were parked along Palermo Drive in Ocean Beach; the others 
were parked throughout Ocean Beach and Loma Portal, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
"There are probably twice those (number of) cars that didn't report the 
vandalism," he said. 
