<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 20-year-old man who was convicted of murdering a cabdriver in Southeast San 
Diego was sentenced Friday to 27 years to life in state prison. 
</P>
<P>
Kevin Antone Johnson of San Diego was also given a consecutive sentence of 6 
years and 8 months in prison for committing two armed robberies. 
</P>
<P>
A Superior Court jury convicted Johnson of first-degree murder in May for the 
May 22, 1989, slaying of Michael Carroll, 25, and of robbing two pizza delivery 
men. 
