<P>
LEADING DISSIDENT WILL NOT BE FREED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A spokesman for Myanmar's military regime indicated that a leading dissident 
under house arrest since last July will not be released next week as scheduled 
and warned her party not to try to declare a government because of its 
landslide election victory. Maj. Gen. Khim Nyunt, head of military 
intelligence, said the junta will not yield to international pressure for the 
release of Aung San Suu Kyi and a transfer of power to her National League for 
Democracy. Suu Kyi, daughter of the country's foremost independence hero when 
it was Burma, was placed under house arrest July 20, 1989. She has never been 
formally charged. 
