<TEXT>
<P>
IBM, Diebold to Combine ATM Operations: IBM and Diebold Inc. said they will 
combine their automated teller machine operations and market the products 
worldwide under a joint venture. 
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the joint venture company and Canton, Ohio-based Diebold 
will market the combined ATM product lines of the two companies in the United 
States, with assistance from IBM, which is based in Armonk, N.Y. IBM will 
market the lines abroad. No dollar value was placed on the deal. The venture 
will develop automated teller machines and other self-service equipment, the 
companies said in a joint statement. 
</P>
