<TEXT>
<P>
Insider Trading Conviction Upheld: U.S. District Judge Stephen Wilson upheld an 
insider trader conviction against Brian J. Callahan, an Anaheim stockbroker, 
and William N. Jackson, a Torrance printer, ruling that the defendants engaged 
in securities fraud when they traded stocks based on information culled from 
advance copies of Business Week magazine. The men were convicted in May of 
conspiring to make profit by trading stocks based on information not yet 
available to the public. The men had challenged the conviction, contending that 
there were no securities violations because they did not obtain information 
directly from companies in which they invested. 
