<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: LINDLEY WINS GOLF TITLE IN NEVADA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leta Lindley of Carlsbad took first place Friday in the Las Vegas Founders' 
Legacy Junior golf tournament at Green Valley, Nev. 
</P>
<P>
Lindley shot a final-round 73 for a three-round total of 220 on the par-72 
Legacy course. Lindley defeated Patti Sinn of Bellflower by three shots. 
</P>
<P>
Todd Demsey of Rancho Sante Fe finished second in the boys' 15-18 division with 
a final total of 216. Demsey shot a final-round 71 and finished eight shots 
behind winner Trip Kuehne of Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego's John Hoffman was eliminated in the second round of match play at 
the Trans-Mississippi Championship at the Oklahoma City Golf and Country Club. 
Hoffman was beaten by Steve Earsley of Lubbock, Tex., 4 and 2. 
</P>
