<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
MAN IN NINJA OUTFIT ROBS PIZZA PARLOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES M. GOMEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An armed robber dressed in a black ninja outfit held up a pizza parlor that was 
about to close, taking more than $200 before disappearing, sheriff's 
authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The bandit, described as a male Caucasian about 5 feet, 10 inches tall, 
disappeared into a large apartment complex near the intersection of Alicia 
Parkway and Paseo de Valencia, said Sheriff's Department spokesman Lt. Bob 
Rivas. 
</P>
<P>
Rivas said the manager and a worker were about to lock the Pizza Hut Restaurant 
on Alicia Parkway at 9:55 p.m. Thursday when the robber entered the store, 
pulled out a chrome-plated revolver and demanded cash. 
</P>
<P>
He fled on foot into an apartment complex. Deputies searched the area but found 
no suspects. 
</P>
<P>
Rivas said that the department has received no prior reports of anybody robbing 
a store or restaurant wearing a black ninja outfit. JAMES M. GOMEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
